{
  "doc_id": "54381",
  "text": "Given the high relative abundances of Marinobacter in all but one of the cryopeg brine and massive ice samples at both genus and OTU levels, a MED analysis was performed to assess whether strain variation occurs between these samples. Approximately, 80% of Marinobacter sequences could be attributed to a single representative oligotype. BLAST analysis of this sequence against the NCBI 16S rRNA database showed 99.6% similarity with Marinobacter psychrophilus strain i20041 cultured from sea ice in the Canadian Basin [CITATION_1] ).",
